`, with a fixed height. * Inside the wrapper is an `` with `height: 100%`. The width of the wrapper should change to match the new width of the image, plus the padding. This behaves as expected in Chrome and IE on both OSX and Win7, but in FF the width of the wrapper seems to remain the same as if no padding was added. Am I missing something, or is this a bug in the implementation of box-sizing in Firefox?
